                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Policeman</hi> 232 <hi rend="italic">Y</hi>). I received information from Aldridge on the 29th December—I found the prisoner on the 31st in a public-house in Holloway—I charged him with stealing 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he denied It at first—on the road to the station he said "I have been lodging at Brockley. The man I was lodging with lent me his shirt that I am now wearing."</p>
